message.content: Yucca treculeana is a species of evergreen shrub native to the southern United States and northern Mexico. It has a single trunk and can grow up to 15 feet tall. The leaves are long and narrow, with sharp tips and a bluish-green color. The flowers are white and bell-shaped, and bloom in the summer. The plant produces a woody fruit that is up to 4 inches long. Yucca treculeana is commonly used in landscaping and can withstand drought and extreme temperatures. It can be found in deserts, rocky slopes, and other arid environments.
